### Maven
### Docker

**File:** `src/main/resources/application-disabled.properties`

```properties
spring.autoconfigure.exclude=org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.jms.activemq.ActiveMQAutoConfiguration
spring.profiles.default=disabled
```

This configuration disables all messaging and database-related auto-configurations.
The disabled profile is set as the default, so no additional arguments are required.








Main Microservice (CRM / Producer)
Project Overview

This repository contains the Main (CRM / Producer) microservice, implemented using Spring Boot and Maven.
The service is containerized using Docker and is configured to start with all external integrations disabled.

Disabled integrations include:
ActiveMQ
Database (JDBC / JPA)
MongoDB
Eureka Client

This allows the application to start and run independently, without requiring external services.

Technology Stack:
Java 21
Spring Boot
Maven
Docker

File: src/main/resources/application-disabled.properties:
```spring.autoconfigure.exclude=org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.jms.activemq.ActiveMQAutoConfiguration,org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.jms.JmsAutoConfiguration,org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.jdbc.DataSourceAutoConfiguration,org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.orm.jpa.HibernateJpaAutoConfiguration,org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.mongo.MongoAutoConfiguration,org.springframework.boot.autoconfigure.data.mongo.MongoDataAutoConfiguration

spring.profiles.default=disabled
```
This configuration disables all messaging and database-related auto-configurations.
The disabled profile is set as the default, so no additional arguments are required at startup.

Dockerfile:
```
# ---- Build stage ----
FROM maven:3.9-eclipse-temurin-21 AS build
WORKDIR /app

COPY pom.xml .
COPY .mvn/ .mvn/
COPY mvnw .
RUN mvn -q -DskipTests dependency:go-offline || true

COPY src ./src
RUN mvn -DskipTests package

# ---- Run stage ----
FROM eclipse-temurin:21-jre
WORKDIR /app

COPY --from=build /app/target/*.jar app.jar
EXPOSE 8080

ENTRYPOINT ["java","-jar","/app/app.jar"]
```

This Dockerfile uses a multi-stage build:
First stage builds the Spring Boot JAR using Maven
Second stage runs the application using a lightweight JRE image

Building the Docker Image
Run the following command from the project root directory:

`docker build -t crm:disabled .`


Running the Application
The application listens on port 8080 inside the container.
To avoid port conflicts, it is mapped to 8081 on the host:
```
docker run -p 8081:8080 crm:disabled
```
Access:
http://localhost:8081
